summary: This is a travel voucher notification email from E2 Solutions to a U.S. Attorney's Office (USANYS) regarding expenses for a trip to Santa Monica, CA from December 15-17, 2019. The trip's purpose is listed as 'R20NYS13257 - U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interviews', indicating it was for federal prosecutors to conduct interviews in the Epstein case.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip to Santa Monica
events.description: A trip was taken to Santa Monica, CA for the purpose of conducting witness interviews in the case of U.S. v. Epstein.

keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher for a trip related to the federal prosecution of Jeffrey Epstein (U.S. v. Epstein).
The trip's stated purpose was 'Witness Interviews' for case R20NYS13257.
The trip occurred from December 15 to December 17, 2019, to Santa Monica, California.
The voucher was sent to the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
The total voucher expenses were $1,360.82 against an estimated trip cost of $1,907.95.
